Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  hired Michael Terry from Oakpoint Advisors LLC as global head of capital
introductions.  Terry will raise money for the firmâ€™s hedge-fund clients
and report to Jon Yalmokas, head of U.S. prime-brokerage sales,
the Charlotte, North Carolina-based bank said in a statement
today. He will be based in New York.  Terry was a founding member of Oakpoint Advisors, a New
York-based firm that advises asset managers. He previously
worked at Morgan Stanley, where he was head of capital
introduction for  North America , and FrontPoint Partners LLC, a
